cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the analysis of encrypted network traffic to identify smartphone apps. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The analysis of network traffic falls under the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the persistence of app fingerprints across devices and app versions, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with the identification of apps, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
